                    <span>The first 2 sections of this book provide detailed information on NT internal functions that are not readily availble elsewhere.  As a sys admin, this takes your knowledge of the OS to a much deeper level than  most.  I'm not a programmer or developer, so I purchased this book just for  the first 2/3 of the info.  Great detail. David W. Glassman, MCSE, MCP+I,  CCNA, W2K Networker.</span>
                  
